Language: en

00:00:04.401 --> 00:00:07.120
TIMOTHY JORDAN: So this is
a talk about Glass--

00:00:07.120 --> 00:00:11.070
in specific, building new
experiences for Glass.

00:00:11.070 --> 00:00:12.330
I'm Timothy Jordan--

00:00:12.330 --> 00:00:12.970
that's me.

00:00:12.970 --> 00:00:14.320
Hi.

00:00:14.320 --> 00:00:17.220
I'm a developer advocate
at Google on Glass.

00:00:17.220 --> 00:00:19.945
If you want to get in touch
online after this, go ahead

00:00:19.945 --> 00:00:25.530
and check out
google.com/+timothyjordan.

00:00:25.530 --> 00:00:27.740
So what are we going to
talk about today?

00:00:27.740 --> 00:00:31.990
Project Glass, of course, which
is part of Google X, the

00:00:31.990 --> 00:00:34.960
moonshot factory at Google.

00:00:34.960 --> 00:00:39.050
Moonshots are these radical
ideas for changing the world

00:00:39.050 --> 00:00:41.600
and improving the way
that we live.

00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:43.980
For more on Google X and
moonshots, you really should

00:00:43.980 --> 00:00:45.620
check out Astro's
talk tomorrow.

00:00:45.620 --> 00:00:47.840
He'll be here in
the afternoon.

00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:52.360
This particular moonshot,
Project Glass, is about our

00:00:52.360 --> 00:00:55.510
relationship to technology.

00:00:55.510 --> 00:00:58.680
It's about technology that's
there when you want it but out

00:00:58.680 --> 00:01:00.740
of the way when you don't.

00:01:00.740 --> 00:01:02.420
What do I mean by that?

00:01:02.420 --> 00:01:05.340
Last night I went
to this event.

00:01:05.340 --> 00:01:07.150
How many of us went to
parties last night?

00:01:07.150 --> 00:01:07.800
Just a few?

00:01:07.800 --> 00:01:08.880
OK, everyone.

00:01:08.880 --> 00:01:12.010
So as people were taking
the stage,

00:01:12.010 --> 00:01:13.205
this weird thing happened.

00:01:13.205 --> 00:01:15.240
And it happens at South By,
but it happens at other

00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:18.890
places, too-- all of these
screens went up into the air.

00:01:18.890 --> 00:01:20.710
Tablets and phones--

00:01:20.710 --> 00:01:24.440
all of these things mediating
these people's experience with

00:01:24.440 --> 00:01:25.750
what was in front of them.

00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:27.870
It's weird because it felt like
they were watching the

00:01:27.870 --> 00:01:30.810
screens instead of the event.

00:01:30.810 --> 00:01:33.400
I mean, we all love technology
and what it can give us-- the

00:01:33.400 --> 00:01:36.080
ability to take and
share pictures--

00:01:36.080 --> 00:01:39.870
but it feels like tech is often
getting in the way more

00:01:39.870 --> 00:01:41.590
than it needs to.

00:01:41.590 --> 00:01:44.860
And that's what we're addressing
with Project Glass.

00:01:44.860 --> 00:01:47.790
It's so that you can still have
access to the technology

00:01:47.790 --> 00:01:52.780
that you love but it doesn't
take you out of the moment.

00:01:52.780 --> 00:01:53.500
I'm going to play a video.

00:01:53.500 --> 00:01:56.545
Many of you have already seen
this video, but I want to play

00:01:56.545 --> 00:01:57.760
it because I love it.

