electrical engineer, and a

00:02:35.690 --> 00:02:39.330
computer scientist are riding
along in a car and the car

00:02:39.330 --> 00:02:41.600
starts making this really
funny noise.

00:02:41.600 --> 00:02:43.160
And the mechanical engineer's
like, well, why

00:02:43.160 --> 00:02:44.350
don't we pull over?

00:02:44.350 --> 00:02:47.760
I'm going to pop the hood and
hit it with a big old hammer.

00:02:47.760 --> 00:02:50.780
The electrical engineer says,
that's kind of crazy.

00:02:50.780 --> 00:02:52.470
How about we pull over and
I'll hook up my computer.

00:02:52.470 --> 00:02:54.170
We'll see what code it's
giving and we'll

00:02:54.170 --> 00:02:55.366
know what to do then.

00:02:55.366 --> 00:02:58.590
The computer scientist
says, oh, all that is

00:02:58.590 --> 00:03:00.020
just so much work.

00:03:00.020 --> 00:03:03.340
We're going to stop the car,
turn it off, get out, get back

00:03:03.340 --> 00:03:06.355
in, turn it on, and see if it's
still making the noise.

00:03:06.355 --> 00:03:10.080
[LAUGHTER]

00:03:10.080 --> 00:03:10.310
TIMOTHY JORDAN: OK.

