00:37:04.120 --> 00:37:06.558
So let's look at this in a
little bit more detail again.

00:37:10.680 --> 00:37:15.330
So this flow starts when I
authorize Gmail to insert

00:37:15.330 --> 00:37:16.930
timeline cards on my Glass.

00:37:19.620 --> 00:37:21.650
Remember that OAuth process
that I told you about?

00:37:21.650 --> 00:37:23.320
Again, this is really
sort of the install

00:37:23.320 --> 00:37:25.070
process for Glass services.

00:37:25.070 --> 00:37:27.900
I go over to the Gmail website
and I say, I want you to send

00:37:27.900 --> 00:37:31.480
the most important emails
as they happen to Glass.

00:37:31.480 --> 00:37:34.660
And it jumps into the OAuth
flow, I give permission, it

00:37:34.660 --> 00:37:36.890
calls back to Gmail,
and it's done.

00:37:36.890 --> 00:37:40.280
But at that moment, Gmail
does a quick thing.

00:37:40.280 --> 00:37:44.160
It inserts a subscription for
all updates on my timeline.

00:37:44.160 --> 00:37:46.210
Remember we talked about
subscriptions?

00:37:46.210 --> 00:37:48.630
Essentially, it's subscribing
to everything I do on the

00:37:48.630 --> 00:37:51.830
timeline that concerns it.

00:37:51.830 --> 00:37:54.310
OK, so now we fast forward
to I'm getting my emails

00:37:54.310 --> 00:37:55.210
throughout the day.

00:37:55.210 --> 00:37:56.980
It inserts timeline cards.

00:37:56.980 --> 00:37:59.510
And on those timeline cards, it
includes just some simple

00:37:59.510 --> 00:38:02.380
text and a creator-- in
this case, Jenny--

00:38:02.380 --> 00:38:05.240
and some speakable text
so that I can have it

00:38:05.240 --> 00:38:07.810
read aloud to me.

00:38:07.810 --> 00:38:11.440
It includes those card options
for Reply and Read Aloud.

00:38:11.440 --> 00:38:14.650
And when I get that email as
a user, I tap on Reply.

00:38:14.650 --> 00:38:18.860
Glass goes into voice dictation,
records what I say,

00:38:18.860 --> 00:38:24.810
and then it notifies Gmail's
subscription endpoint.

00:38:24.810 --> 00:38:26.620
Remember, it subscribed
and then it sends the

